rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: An application
rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: Application

rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: A compressed file. May contain other files or folder inside.
rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: Archive

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: Uncompressed size of the content of a compressed file.
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: uncompressedSize

rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: A file entity inside an archive.
rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: ArchiveItem

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: States if a given resource is password-protected.
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: isPasswordProtected

rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: A file attached to another data object. Many data formats allow for attachments: emails, vcards, ical events, id3 and exif...
rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: Attachment

rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: A file containing audio content
rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: Audio

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: Number of channels. This property is to be used directly if no detailed information is necessary. Otherwise use more detailed subproperties.
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: channels

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: Number of side channels
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: sideChannels

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: Number of Low Frequency Expansion (subwoofer) channels.
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: lfeChannels

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: The amount of samples in an audio clip.
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: sampleCount

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: Amount of bits in each audio sample.
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: bitsPerSample

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: Number of front channels.
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: frontChannels

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: The amount of audio samples per second.
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: sampleRate

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: The average overall bitrate of a media container. (i.e. the size of the piece of media in bits, divided by it's duration expressed in seconds).
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: averageBitrate

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: Number of rear channels.
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: rearChannels

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: Gain of media
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: Gain

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: Peak Gain of media
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: Peak Gain

rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: A bookmark of a webbrowser. Use nie:title for the name/label, nie:contentCreated to represent the date when the user added the bookmark, and nie:contentLastModified for modifications. nfo:bookmarks to store the link.
rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: Bookmark

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: The address of the linked object. Usually a web URI.
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: link

rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: A folder with bookmarks of a webbrowser. Use nfo:containsBookmark to relate Bookmarks. Folders can contain subfolders, use containsBookmarkFolder to relate them.
rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: Bookmark Folder

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: The folder contains a bookmark folder.
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: contains folder

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: The folder contains a bookmark.
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: contains bookmark

rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: Type of compression. Instances of this class represent the limited set of values allowed for the nfo:compressionType property.
rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: CompressionType

rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: A Cursor.
rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: Cursor

rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: A superclass for all entities, whose primary purpose is to serve as containers for other data object. They usually don't have any 'meaning' by themselves. Examples include folders, archives and optical disc images.
rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: DataContainer

rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: A file entity that has been deleted from the original source. Usually such entities are stored within various kinds of 'Trash' or 'Recycle Bin' folders.
rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: DeletedResource

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: The original location of the deleted resource.
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: originalLocation

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: The date and time of the deletion.
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: deletionDate

rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: A generic document. A common superclass for all documents on the desktop.
rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: Document

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: Section titles and figure descriptions of the document.
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: Table of contents

rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: A file embedded in another data object. There are many ways in which a file may be embedded in another one. Use this class directly only in cases if none of the subclasses gives a better description of your case.
rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: EmbeddedFileDataObject

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: The encoding used for the Embedded File. Examples might include BASE64 or UUEncode
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: encoding

rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: The equipment used to create media
rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: Equipment

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: The manufacturer of the equipment
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: Manufacturer

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: The model of the equipment
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: Model

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: The software of the equipment
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: Equipment software

rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: An executable file.
rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: Executable

rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: A resource containing a finite sequence of bytes with arbitrary information, that is available to a computer program and is usually based on some kind of durable storage. A file is durable in the sense that it remains available for programs to use after the current program has finished.
rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: FileDataObject

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: Time when the file was last accessed.
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: fileLastAccessed

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: File creation date
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: fileCreated

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: The size of the file in bytes. For compressed files it means the size of the packed file, not of the contents. For folders it means the aggregated size of all contained files and folders
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: fileSize

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: A string containing the permissions of a file. A feature common in many UNIX-like operating systems.
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: permissions

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: Name of the file, together with the extension
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: fileName

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: URL of the file. It points at the location of the file. In cases where creating a simple file:// or http:// URL for a file is difficult (e.g. for files inside compressed archives) the applications are encouraged to use conventions defined by Apache Commons VFS Project at http://jakarta.apache.org/ commons/ vfs/ filesystems.html.
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: fileUrl

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: Links the file with it's hash value.
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: hasHash

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: The owner of the file as defined by the file system access rights feature.
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: fileOwner

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: last modification date
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: fileLastModified

rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: A fingerprint of the file, generated by some hashing function.
rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: FileHash

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: The actual value of the hash.
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: hashValue

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: Name of the algorithm used to compute the hash value. Examples might include CRC32, MD5, SHA, TTH etc.
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: hashAlgorithm

rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: A filesystem. Examples of filesystems include hard disk partitions, removable media, but also images thereof stored in files.
rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: Filesystem

rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: An image of a filesystem. Instances of this class may include CD images, DVD images or hard disk partition images created by various pieces of software (e.g. Norton Ghost)
rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: FilesystemImage

rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: A folder/directory. Examples of folders include folders on a filesystem and message folders in a mailbox.
rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: Folder

rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: A font.
rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: Font

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: The name of the font family.
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: fontFamily

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: The foundry, the organization that created the font.
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: foundry

rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: A partition on a hard disk
rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: HardDiskPartition

rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: User guides and similar to assist the user
rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: Help document

rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: A HTML document, may contain links to other files.
rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: HtmlDocument

rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: An Icon (regardless of whether it's a raster or a vector icon. A resource representing an icon could have two types (Icon and Raster, or Icon and Vector) if required.
rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: Icon

rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: A file containing an image.
rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: Image

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: Vertical resolution of an Image (if printed). Expressed in DPI
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: verticalResolution

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: Horizontal resolution of an image (if printed). Expressed in DPI.
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: horizontalResolution

rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: A piece of media content. This class may be used to express complex media containers with many streams of various media content (both aural and visual).
rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: Media

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: A common superproperty for all properties signifying the amount of atomic media data units. Examples of subproperties may include sampleCount and frameCount.
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: count

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: Duration of a media piece.
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: duration

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: Device (maker/model) used to capture the image/video
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: Device

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: The type of the compression. Values include, lossy and lossless.
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: compressionType

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: Connects a media container with a single media stream contained within.
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: hasMediaStream

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: A common superproperty for all properties signifying the amount of bits for an atomic unit of data. Examples of subproperties may include bitsPerSample and bitsPerPixel
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: bitDepth

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: The name of the codec necessary to decode a piece of media.
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: codec

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: The contains the name of the person or organisation that encoded the media
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: encodedBy

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: The type of the bitrate. Examples may include CBR and VBR.
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: bitrateType

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: The average overall bitrate of a media container. (i.e. the size of the piece of media in bits, divided by it's duration expressed in seconds).
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: averageBitrate

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: Genre of media
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: Genre

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: Equipment used to create the media
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: Device
Increase if the media is skip while playing

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: Link between to different version of the same media. This is used for instances in uPnp where the server can provide the same video in different resolutions and codecs
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: Alternative media

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: DLNA profile of the content, like MP3, MPEG_TS_HD_US, LPCM etc
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: DLNA profile

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: Tells the uPnP MediaServer (e.g. Rygel) whether to export/share the resource or not
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: uPnP shared

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: Hidden for the MTP protocol
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: Hidden

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: Following MTP spec, credits contains... FIXME
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: MTP credits

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: Following MTP spec, this property can contain a free text taking about creator of the Media
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: MTP Creator

rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: A single node in the list of media files contained within an MediaList instance. This class is intended to provide a type all those links have. In valid NRL untyped resources cannot be linked. There are no properties defined for this class but the application may expect rdf:first and rdf:last links. The former points to the DataObject instance, interpreted as Media the latter points at another MediaFileListEntr. At the end of the list there is a link to rdf:nil.
rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: MediaFileListEntry

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: Position of an entry in a list. Double, to optimize the poor insertions
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: list position

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: URI to the element in certain position of the list
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: Entry content

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: URI to the element in certain position of the list
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: Entry URL

rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: A file containing a list of media files.e.g. a playlist
rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: MediaList

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: This property is intended to point to an RDF list of MediaFiles.
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: hasMediaFileListEntry

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: Number of entries in the list. Optimize some common queries
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: entry Counter

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: Sum of the duration of all items in the list. Optimize some common queries. In seconds
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: List duration

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: A certain item belongs to a media list. This can reflect that a song is in a playlist, an image or video in an Album
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: Media list entry

rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: A stream of multimedia content, usually contained within a media container such as a movie (containing both audio and video) or a DVD (possibly containing many streams of audio and video). Most common interpretations for such a DataObject include Audio and Video.
rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: MediaStream

rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: A MindMap, created by a mind-mapping utility. Examples might include FreeMind or mind mapper.
rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: MindMap

rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: An OperatingSystem
rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: OperatingSystem

rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: Orientation enum
rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: Orientation enum

rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: A file containing a text document, that is unambiguously divided into pages. Examples might include PDF, DOC, PS', DVI etc.
rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: PaginatedTextDocument

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: Number of pages.
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: pageCount

rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: A file containing plain text (ASCII, Unicode or other encodings). Examples may include TXT, HTML, XML, program source code etc.
rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: PlainTextDocument

rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: A Presentation made by some presentation software (Corel Presentations, OpenOffice Impress, MS Powerpoint etc.)
rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: Presentation

rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: A raster image.
rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: RasterImage

rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: A file data object stored at a remote location. Don't confuse this class with a RemotePortAddress. This one applies to a particular resource, RemotePortAddress applies to an address, that can have various interpretations.
rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: RemoteDataObject

rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: An address specifying a remote host and port. Such an address can be interpreted in many ways (examples of such interpretations include mailboxes, websites, remote calendars or filesystems), depending on an interpretation, various kinds of data may be extracted from such an address.
rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: RemotePortAddress

rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: A piece of software. Examples may include applications and the operating system. This interpretation most commonly applies to SoftwareItems.
rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: Software

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: States that a piece of software is in conflict with another piece of software.
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: conflicts

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: States that a piece of software supercedes another piece of software.
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: supercedes

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: Icon of the software
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: SoftwareIcon

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: Command to launch the software
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: SoftwareCmdLine

rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: An application
rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: Application

rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: A software category
rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: Software

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: Icon of the software
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: SoftwareIcon

rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: A DataObject representing a piece of software. Examples of interpretations of a SoftwareItem include an Application and an OperatingSystem.
rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: SoftwareItem

rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: A service published by a piece of software, either by an operating system or an application. Examples of such services may include calendar, addresbook and mailbox managed by a PIM application. This category is introduced to distinguish between data available directly from the applications (Via some Interprocess Communication Mechanisms) and data available from files on a disk. In either case both DataObjects would receive a similar interpretation (e.g. a Mailbox) and wouldn't differ on the content level.
rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: SoftwareService

rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: Code in a compilable or interpreted programming language.
rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: SourceCode

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: The amount of character in comments i.e. characters ignored by the compiler/interpreter.
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: commentCharacterCount

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: Name of a class defined in the source code file.
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: definesClass

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: A name of a function/method defined in the given source code file.
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: definesFunction

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: Name of a global variable defined within the source code file.
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: definesGlobalVariable

rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: A spreadsheet, created by a spreadsheet application. Examples might include Gnumeric, OpenOffice Calc or MS Excel.
rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: Spreadsheet

rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: A text document
rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: TextDocument

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: The amount of words in a text document.
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: wordCount

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: The amount of lines in a text document
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: lineCount

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: The amount of characters in the document.
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: characterCount

rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: Represents a container for deleted files, a feature common in modern operating systems.
rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: Trash

rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: A video file.
rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: Video

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: Amount of video frames per second.
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: frameRate

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: The amount of frames in a video sequence.
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: frameCount

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: The average overall bitrate of a media container. (i.e. the size of the piece of media in bits, divided by it's duration expressed in seconds).
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: averageBitrate

rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: File containing visual content.
rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: Visual

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: Visual content aspect ratio. (Width divided by Height)
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: aspectRatio

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: Specifies the direction of travelling while capturing image/video. The range of values from 0.00 to 359.99 (where 0 is due North, 90 is East, 180 South and 270 is West)
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: Heading

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: Vertical inclination of the camera while capturing the image, in angles starting on 0 as horizontal, positive numbers pointing up, negative angles pointing down
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: Tilt

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: True if the image is interlaced, false if not.
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: interlaceMode

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: Visual content height in pixels.
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: height

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: Visual content width in pixels.
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: width

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: Amount of bits used to express the color of each pixel.
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: colorDepth

rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: A web history entry
rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: Web History

rdf:Property.rdfs:label: Domain for a web history entry
Uri for a web history entry

rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: A website, usually a container for remote resources, that may be interpreted as HTMLDocuments, images or other types of content.
rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: Website

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: Models the containment relations between Files and Folders (or CompressedFiles).
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: belongsToContainer

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: Might change (IE of DataObject property?)
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: Is content encrypted
